<Center>

## Sorting Cards

</Center>

Pick the deck of cards in your palm and shuffle these till these have mixed up well and the order has got disturbed. Now, follow these steps to get these cards in their right order:

1. Insert a stick in the rightmost hole or slit (whichever is in the rightmost) and pull the cards up.
2. Some cards (say Type I) will get attached to the stick and rest of the cards tend to fall down (say Type II) which you hold up in your palm.
3. Place these cards (Type I) ahead of the remaining cards (Type II).
4. Now, place the stick in the second rightmost hole, again there will be some Type I cards and Type II cards. Repeat step iii.
5. Repeat the process until the stick makes way to the leftmost hole/slit and club the Type I cards and place these cards ahead of remaining cards. The cards will be arranged in order.

### Understand the Sorting Algorithm

The explanation lies in the video itself. Let's understand how the stick trick works to sort the cards in right way (The pictures represent sorting for cards numbered from 1 to 8):

- Before inserting the stick in the rightmost hole/slit. (Image 2)
- After inserting the stick in the rightmost hole/slit and clubbing the hanging cards (Type I) together. (Image 3)

<Center>
<img src="CURRENT/image_23.png" alt="Image 2 and 3: Sorting demonstration" width="60%">
</Center>

So after this step the numbers 0,2,4,6 which have a 0 in the rightmost place in binary representation will be before 1,3,5,7 respectively which have a 1 in the rightmost place.

(iii) Before inserting the stick in the second rightmost hole/slit (or middle hole/slit) (Image 4).

<Center>
<img src="CURRENT/image_45.png" alt="Image 4" width="60%">
</Center>

(iv) After inserting the stick in the second rightmost hole/slit and clubbing the Type I cards together (Image 5).

After this step the numbers 0, 1 will be placed before the numbers 2, 3. Similarly 4, 5 will be placed before 6, 7. This placement does not disturb the order established in step ii.

(v) Before inserting the stick in the leftmost hole (last hole/slit) (Image 6).

<Center>
<img src="CURRENT/image_67.png" alt="Image 6" width="60%">
</Center>

(vi) After inserting the stick in the leftmost hole and clubbing the Type I cards together.

After this step the numbers 0, 1, 2, 3 will be placed before the numbers 4, 5, 6, 7 thus sorting the cards and without disturbing the previous order.

