In ternary approach, we would use two different sticks: one stick/needle (say ST1) which can be inserted in the hole (H), half slit (S1) and complete slit (S2) but can escape (vertically) only through S1 and S2; and another stick (say ST2) which can be inserted in H, S1 and S2 but can escape (vertically) only through S2.

