</table>

**Table 6** (Relationship between sticks and holes/slits)

Can't escape: X; Can escape: O

</Center>

Make punches corresponding to three holes (see Image 1) in your alphabet cards and shuffle the cards. Follow these steps to get your cards in right order:

1. Insert ST1 into the rightmost hole/slit and club Type I cards together and place these ahead of the remaining cards.
2. Insert ST2 again into the rightmost hole/slit and club Type I cards together and place these ahead of remaining cards.
3. Repeat the steps (i) and (ii) (first ST1 and then ST2) for the middle hole/slit, club the Type I cards together and place them ahead of the remaining cards.
4. Repeat the process until ST2 makes way to the leftmost hole/slit, clubbing the Type I cards together and placing them ahead of the remaining cards. The cards will get arranged in proper order.

